<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="337" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1332,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,494,1332,1357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Redescription of adult male:</emphasis>
Color in alcohol light brown, covered with golden yellow pubescence, wings light brown, dorsum of head dark brown, with 9 dark brown setal warts. Length from tip of head to apices of folded forewings 
<quantity box="[270,388,1404,1429]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.225" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="12.25">12.25 mm</quantity>
; length of each antenna 
<quantity box="[663,746,1404,1428]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
; maxillary palps each 
<quantity box="[999,1086,1404,1429]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long, 2nd segment longer than 3rd and 4th together, 5th segment as long as segments 1st–4th together; labial palps each 
<quantity box="[1155,1256,1439,1464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="0.75">0.75 mm</quantity>
long. Length of each forewing 
<quantity box="[317,395,1476,1500]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
(n = 2); length of each hind wing 
<quantity box="[778,881,1476,1501]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="8.25">8.25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1332,2005]" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[387,532,1511,1536]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1934,1956]" captionTargetBox="[225,1370,219,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,193,1912]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 21–30. Hydropsyche spp., male genitalia. 21–25, H. harpagofalcata Mey: 21, left lateral; 22, dorsal; 23, right inferior appendage, ventral; 24, phallus, left lateral; 25, phallus, ventral. 26–30, H. hajinensis sp. nov.: 26, left lateral; 27, dorsal; 28, right inferior appendage, ventral; 29, phallus, left lateral; 30, phallus, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1118022/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Figs. 21–25</figureCitation>
): Abdominal segment IX longitudinally short, anterolateral margins convex; dorsomedian keel directed posterad, digitate in dorsal view, dorsally and laterally granulose, positioned posteriorly; anteroventral margin straight, anterodorsal margin notched in dorsal view; posterolateral lobe on each side round, posterior spine row not continuous with setal row on posterolateral slope of median keel. Depression between segment IX and tergum X U-shaped. Body of tergum X longitudinally short, nearly quadrangular in lateral view; quadrate in dorsal view; apicoventral setose lobes modified into rounded projections directed posterad in lateral and dorsal views, setae present on dorsal surface; dorsal interlobular gap minute. Inferior appendages each 2- segmented, basal segment (coxopodite), long, broad basally, slightly dilating distally from mid length in lateral view; almost straight in ventral view; apical segment (harpago) very small, acute apically in lateral view; curved mesad in ventral view. Phallic apparatus simple, convex ventrally then concave for short distance subapically in lateral view; endotheca with pair of broad, incurved, acute apices in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
