<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="338" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1332,2005]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="338" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1944,1969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mey 1996" authorityName="Mey" authorityYear="1996" box="[614,972,1944,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napaea">
<emphasis box="[614,850,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Hydropsyche napaea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mey" box="[857,972,1944,1969]" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" refString="Mey, W. (1996) Zur Kenntnis der Hydropsyche pluvialis - Gruppe in Sudostasien (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). Entomologische Zeitschrift, 106, 144 - 152." type="journal article" year="1996">Mey 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[986,1085,1944,1969]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol 2000" authorityName="Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askalaphos">
<emphasis box="[1147,1307,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">H. askalaphos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Malicky" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" refString="Malicky, H. &amp; Chantaramongkol, P. (2000) Ein Beitrag zur Kenntnis asiatischer Hydropsyche - Arten (Trichoptera, Hydropsychidae). (Zugleich Arbeit Nr. 29 uber thailandische Kocherfliegen). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 32, 791 - 860." type="journal article" year="2000">Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol 2000</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[430,536,1980,2005]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">Thailand</collectingCountry>
). In 
<taxonomicName authority="Mey" authorityName="Mey" box="[586,853,1980,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="337" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harpagofalcata">
<emphasis box="[586,794,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="337">H. harpagofalcata</emphasis>
Mey
</taxonomicName>
, the dorsomedian keel of segment IX is much more produced and rounded apically whereas it is wide and broad in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malicky &amp; Chantaramongkol" authorityYear="2000" box="[878,1040,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askalaphos">
<emphasis box="[878,1040,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">H. askalaphos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The shape of segment IX is quite similar in 
<taxonomicName box="[263,470,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harpagofalcata">
<emphasis box="[263,470,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">H. harpagofalcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mey" authorityYear="1996" box="[524,640,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napaea">
<emphasis box="[524,640,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">H. napaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in lateral view. However, the rounded dorsomedian keel of segment IX and the shape of the apical part of the phallus (width twice its length) in 
<taxonomicName box="[958,1165,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harpagofalcata">
<emphasis box="[958,1165,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">H. harpagofalcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
makes the latter distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mey" authorityYear="1996" box="[212,329,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Hydropsyche" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="338" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="napaea">
<emphasis box="[212,329,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="338">H. napaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which dorsomedian keel is pointed and the apical part of the phallus is twice as long as wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
